      {
         "id": "SECTION_historical",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<h3>Exploring System Limitations in Historical Records</h3><p>The advent of writing systems approximately, 5500 years ago marks a pivotal moment in human history (<htcite0>). It is crucial to acknowledge that records prior to this era are sparse, limiting our ability to access detailed information about ancient civilizations. However, it's essential to recognize that historical narratives may be shaped by various factors, including societal needs and cultural biases. For instance, accounts of Sumerian kings often feature exaggerated reigns, such as that of Alaljar, who purportedly ruled for an astonishing 36,000 years (<htcite1> ; <htcite2>). </p><p>It is not uncommon to see people tracing their lineage until reach an initial couple relying on written records (<htcite3>). Is this family tree inaccurate? The direct answer to this question is no, but is this answer a contradiction for what genetic is showing? The advent of genetic research has shed new light on our understanding of ancestry. DNA analysis can reveal unexpected familial connections and disprove long-held beliefs about lineage. Thus, while traditional family trees may be accurate based on historical sources, they may lack completeness or accuracy when compared to contemporary scientific knowledge.</p><p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\" id=\"myFirstReflection\"><b>Reflection 1: About genealogical trees</b><br /><br />Is it better to have a genealogical tree with ancestors we aspire to have?<br />Or is it better to have a genealogical tree with ancestors we actually have?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "22c3824d-559b-4341-b999-cd0bb39c6246",
                     "text": "Encyclopedia Britannica",
                     "page": "History of writing systems",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "12",
                        "day": "05"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "01ee98b4-e72d-47dd-81ee-138b20ac631d",
                     "text": "Fink, Sebastian and Sazonov, Vladimir",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
