            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\" style=\"background-color: #D7FFE4;\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\" style=\"background-color: #D7FFE4;\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-infinity\" style=\"font-size: 1em;\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\" id=\"GenealogicalZero\" style=\"background-color: #D7FFE4;\"><b>Mathematics in History</b><br /><br />Mathematical limits (<htcite0>) help us filter personal desires.<br /><br />When no documentation or chronicles exist, the primary sources that could establish connections hold the same maximum and minimum value—zero (0), which indicates emptiness (<htcite1>). As a result, proving connections becomes impossible. Although some authors may attempt to establish links by formulating hypotheses, the lack of documentation allows us to categorically state that we are dealing with a hypothetical level that does not permit the formulation of a theory.</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "18a901e4-3da3-45d8-a239-fb551e78698e",
                     "text": "Natural Limits",
                     "page": "",
