      {
         "id": "SECTION_conclusion",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<h3>Conclusion</h3><p>In this exploration, we have delved into our current understanding of the emergence of our species, <i>Homo sapiens</i>, estimated to have arisen approximately 250,000 years ago. This timeline encompasses approximately 8064 generations since the advent of <i>Homo sapiens</i> (<htcite0>). Additionally, we have considered the estimated number of generations expected since the discovery of writing systems, taking into account genetic constraints.</p><p>Furthermore, our study has extended to include other species within our genealogical family, notably <i>Homo neanderthalensis</i>, which coexisted with us until their extinction.</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "2e75a27c-2ea7-4f09-bf86-578338fc2518",
                     "text": "Groeneveld, E.",
